entries.title: Tanks Alone Won’t Turn the Tide of the War in Ukraine
entries.description: The United States will have to step up its training program to ensure the Ukrainian military can use all the Western-provided equipment effectively.

entries.title: Expert Panel Votes for Stricter Rules on Risky Virus Research
entries.description: The White House will decide whether to adopt the panel’s recommendations on so-called gain of function experiments.

entries.title: China’s Oil and Gas Use Fell in 2022 for First Time in Decades
entries.description: Pandemic lockdowns curbed Chinese energy demand, but the International Energy Agency expects a rebound this year.

entries.title: Eurostar, Symbol of a Connected Europe, Is Plagued by Brexit Hurdles
entries.description: The high-speed train service under the English Channel is leaving many seats unfilled, rather than risk delays caused by more rigorous passport checks for Britons.

entries.title: At Least 5 Killed in Attack in East Jerusalem
entries.description: Police said a gunman killed the people at a small synagogue, before being killed himself by police fire.

entries.title: Alan Cumming Returns British Honor Over ‘Toxicity of Empire’
entries.description: The Scottish actor Alan Cumming said that he returned his Order of the British Empire, or O.B.E., in protest of the role of the monarchy and empire. He’s not the first celebrity to do so.

entries.title: Russia says it will switch four occupied Ukrainian regions to Moscow time.
entries.description: Russia, which has many time zones, is seeking to integrate the regions after illegally annexing them in September.

entries.title: Álvaro Colom, Guatemalan President Who Fought for the Indigenous, Dies at 71
entries.description: He expanded access to education and health care in Indigenous villages and provided aid to the poor in a country scarred by deep inequalities and decades of civil war.

entries.title: AP Retreats From ‘the French’ Stylebook Guidance
entries.description: The Associated Press offends French sensibilities and retreats from a piece of descriptive advice.

entries.title: Gunman Attacks Azerbaijan Embassy in Tehran, Killing the Head of Security
entries.description: Iranian officials blamed the assault, which also wounded two guards, on “personal motivations,” while the Azerbaijani authorities called it a “terrorist attack.” A suspect is in custody.

entries.title: Russia Outlaws Meduza, a Leading Independent News Site
entries.description: The move made Meduza the latest journalistic outlet to fall victim to the Kremlin’s efforts to suppress criticism.

entries.title: ‘We Have to Come Here to Be Seen’: Protesters Descend on Lima
entries.description: Peru’s unrest continues unabated as the demonstrations move to the country’s capital and the government doubles down on portraying demonstrators as pawns for nefarious interests.

entries.title: New Zealand Floods: Rain and Flooding Batters Auckland
entries.description: Auckland declared a local state of emergency as a devastating deluge prompted chaotic scenes, evacuations and power outages.

entries.title: Polar Vortex Drives a Cold Snap in Asia
entries.description: An exceptionally cold January has brought the region misery and snarled travel. Experts blame the same arctic system that hit the United States last month.

entries.title: Russia Strikes Another Blow to Press Freedom With Move Against News Site
entries.description: Officials labeled the independent site Meduza, which is based in Latvia, an “undesirable organization,” effectively outlawing its content.

entries.title: Teenage Rapper, Rooted in Mapuche Identity, Roars for Indigenous Rights
entries.description: MC Millaray, 16, an emerging music star in Chile, uses her fierce lyrics to convey five centuries of struggles by the country’s largest Indigenous group against European colonizers.

entries.title: Ukraine Corruption Scandal Stokes Longstanding Aid Concerns in U.S.
entries.description: A top State Department official said the ouster of several Ukrainian officials this week after corruption charges “sends a very strong signal.”

entries.title: Will U.K. Rejection of Scottish Gender Bill Bolster Independence Movement?
entries.description: The decision left Scottish politicians angered by what they saw as London’s thwarting the will of their Parliament, possibly handing independence backers a potent weapon.

entries.title: Your Friday Briefing
entries.description: A barrage of Russian missiles across Ukraine.

entries.title: Is Australia Day Approaching a Tipping Point?
entries.description: A majority of Australian adults under 35 support changing the date from Jan. 26.

entries.title: In Wave of Strikes, Russian Missiles Kill 12 Across Ukraine
entries.description: Russia’s forces once again pounded energy infrastructure and other civilian sites, a day after the United States and Germany pledged to send dozens of tanks to Ukraine.
